    "answer_id" : 44925111,
    "question_id" : 4502605,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>as @Jérémy Reynaud pointing out, as described in this <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/a/18279169/43051\">answer</a>, the safest way to set the left drawable without changing the values of the other drawables (top, right, and bottom) is by using the previous values from the button with <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/TextView.html#setCompoundDrawablesWithIntrinsicBounds(android.graphics.drawable.Drawable,%20android.graphics.drawable.Drawable,%20android.graphics.drawable.Drawable,%20android.graphics.drawable.Drawable)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">setCompoundDrawablesWithIntrinsicBounds</a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Drawable leftDrawable = getContext().getResources()\n                          .getDrawable(R.drawable.yourdrawable);\n\n// Or use ContextCompat\n// Drawable leftDrawable = ContextCompat.getDrawable(getContext(),\n//                                        R.drawable.yourdrawable);\n\nDrawable[] drawables = button.getCompoundDrawables();\nbutton.setCompoundDrawablesWithIntrinsicBounds(leftDrawable,drawables[1],\n                                               drawables[2], drawables[3]);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So all your previous drawable will be preserved.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3661982,
      "reputation" : 3160,
      "user_id" : 3051503,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/2rNTe.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Muhaiminur Rahman",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3051503/muhaiminur-rahman"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1527135832,
    "last_edit_date" : 1527135832,
    "creation_date" : 1527135692,
    "answer_id" : 50500925,
    "question_id" : 4502605,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Might be helpful:</p>\n\n<pre><code>TextView location;\nlocation=(TextView)view.findViewById(R.id.complain_location);\n//in parameter (left,top,right,bottom) any where you wnat to put\nlocation.setCompoundDrawablesWithIntrinsicBounds(0, 0, R.drawable.arrow,0);\n</code></pre>\n"
